The company IBM (International Business Machines) founded hundreds of years ago had a fairly complicated name - Computing Tableling Recording Corporation.
The name IBM took it only in 1924 - originally it was a brand name for a branch in Canada and South America.
The foundation for the later company IBM laid the merger of four companies, whose history dates back to the 1980s of the 19th century.
They own technologies such as the famous card clocks for recording the start and end of work.
The architects of this new company were Charles Ranlett Flint, who was also chairman of the Supervisory Board by 1930.
And it was Flint who set up the head of the competition firm Thomas J. Watson to help him in the management of the company.
This leader then even put the founders of IBM into the shadows - based on Watson's ideas, the unbeatable culture and identity of the company.
Watson led the company until 1952.
IBM, began, as the name has already betrayed, with the production and distribution of all possible machines for trade - from sausage and cheese cuttings, to cassettes.
In the first four decades in which Watson led the company, he doubled its sales to nine million dollars and the company expanded to and beyond all continents.
Watson was so essential to the company that he sat in the chair for forty years, only then he was dissolved by his son, Thomas Watson Junior.
Under this direction IBM began to work on the development of artificial intelligence and also developed the first programming language.
In the 1960s IBM's technicians and computers of NASA helped fly to all - to Mercury and Saturn and in 1969 also the famous flight of man to the moon.
Meanwhile, in 1964 IBM developed the first computer family with the same computer architecture - the IBM System/360 series.
A classic PC that defined the computer standard at that time came into the market in 1981 under the name IBM 5150.
Twenty years later, IBM sold its computer production to the Chinese company Lenovo, but on the other hand, it bought the consultant part of PricewaterhouseCoopers and thus became fully involved in the business of consulting services and services with high added value.
